            <div id="cite-apa" class="tab selected" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-0" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
                <div class="rendering rendering_researchoutput  rendering_researchoutput_apa rendering_contributiontojournal rendering_apa rendering_contributiontojournal_apa">Saber, A. T.<a rel="Person" href="https://orbit.dtu.dk/en/persons/niels-hadrup/" class="link"><span>, Hadrup, N.</span></a>, Williams, A., Mortensen, A., Szarek, J., Kyjovska, Z., Kurz, A., Jacobsen, N. R., Wallin, H., Halappanavar, S.<a rel="Person" href="https://orbit.dtu.dk/en/persons/ulla-birgitte-vogel/" class="link"><span>, &amp; Vogel, U.</span></a> (2022). <a rel="ContributionToJournal" href="https://orbit.dtu.dk/en/publications/unchanged-pulmonary-toxicity-of-zno-nanoparticles-formulated-in-a/" class="link"><span>Unchanged pulmonary toxicity of ZnO nanoparticles formulated in a liquid matrix for glass coating</span></a>. <a rel="Journal" href="#" class="link"><span><em>Nanotoxicology</em></span></a>, <em>16</em>(6-8), 812-827. <a onclick="window.open(this.href, '_blank','noopener,noreferrer'); return false;" href="https://doi.org/10.1080/17435390.2022.2152751" class="link"><span>https://doi.org/10.1080/17435390.2022.2152751</span></a></div>
            </div>
        
            <div id="cite-author" class="tab " role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-1" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
                <div class="rendering rendering_researchoutput  rendering_researchoutput_author rendering_contributiontojournal rendering_author rendering_contributiontojournal_author">Saber, Anne Thoustrup <a rel="Person" href="https://orbit.dtu.dk/en/persons/niels-hadrup/" class="link"><span> ; Hadrup, Niels</span></a> ; Williams, Andrew et al. / <a rel="ContributionToJournal" href="https://orbit.dtu.dk/en/publications/unchanged-pulmonary-toxicity-of-zno-nanoparticles-formulated-in-a/" class="link"><span><strong>Unchanged pulmonary toxicity of ZnO nanoparticles formulated in a liquid matrix for glass coating</strong></span></a>. In: <a rel="Journal" href="#" class="link"><span>Nanotoxicology</span></a>. 2022 ; Vol. 16, No. 6-8. pp. 812-827.</div>
            </div>
        
            <div id="cite-BIBTEX" class="tab " role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-2" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
                <div class="rendering rendering_researchoutput  rendering_researchoutput_bibtex rendering_contributiontojournal rendering_bibtex rendering_contributiontojournal_bibtex"><div>@article{4528db0c85ab476eb342d112fbb7ff51,</div><div>  title     = "Unchanged pulmonary toxicity of ZnO nanoparticles formulated in a liquid matrix for glass coating",</div><div>  abstract  = "The inclusion of nanoparticles can increase the quality of certain products. One application is the inclusion of Zinc oxide (ZnO) nanoparticles in a glass coating matrix to produce a UV-absorbing coating for glass sheets. Yet, the question is whether the inclusion of ZnO in the matrix induces toxicity at low exposure levels. To test this, mice were given single intratracheal instillation of 1) ZnO powder (ZnO), 2) ZnO in a glass matrix coating in its liquid phase (ZnO-Matrix), and 3) the matrix with no ZnO (Matrix). Doses of ZnO were 0.23, 0.67, and 2 µg ZnO/mouse. ZnO Matrix doses had equal amounts of ZnO, while Matrix was adjusted to have an equal volume of matrix as ZnO Matrix. Post-exposure periods were 1, 3, or 28 d. Endpoints were pulmonary inflammation as bronchoalveolar lavage (BAL) fluid cellularity, genotoxicity in lung and liver, measured by comet assay, histopathology of lung and liver, and global gene expression in lung using microarrays. Neutrophil numbers were increased to a similar extent with ZnO and ZnO-Matrix at 1 and 3 d. Only weak genotoxicity without dose-response effects was observed in the lung. Lung histology showed an earlier onset of inflammation in material-exposed groups as compared to controls. Microarray analysis showed a stronger response in terms of the number of differentially regulated genes in ZnO-Matrix exposed mice as compared to Matrix only. Activated canonical pathways included inflammatory and cardiovascular ones. In conclusion, the pulmonary toxicity of ZnO was not changed by formulation in a liquid matrix for glass coating.",</div><div>  keywords  = "Zinc oxide, Comet assay, Genotoxicity, Advanced materials, Gene expression",</div><div>  author    = "Saber, \{Anne Thoustrup\} and Niels Hadrup and Andrew Williams and Alicja Mortensen and Jozef Szarek and Zdenka Kyjovska and Alexander Kurz and Jacobsen, \{Nicklas Raun\} and H{\aa}kan Wallin and Sabina Halappanavar and Ulla Vogel",</div><div>  year      = "2022",</div><div>  doi       = "10.1080/17435390.2022.2152751",</div><div>  language  = "English",</div><div>  volume    = "16",</div><div>  pages     = "812--827",</div><div>  journal   = "Nanotoxicology",</div><div>  issn      = "1743-5390",</div><div>  publisher = "Taylor and Francis Ltd.",</div><div>  number    = "6-8",</div><p>}</p></div>
            </div>
        
            <div id="cite-harvard" class="tab " role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-3" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
                <div class="rendering rendering_researchoutput  rendering_researchoutput_harvard rendering_contributiontojournal rendering_harvard rendering_contributiontojournal_harvard">Saber, AT<a rel="Person" href="https://orbit.dtu.dk/en/persons/niels-hadrup/" class="link"><span>, Hadrup, N</span></a>, Williams, A, Mortensen, A, Szarek, J, Kyjovska, Z, Kurz, A, Jacobsen, NR, Wallin, H, Halappanavar, S<a rel="Person" href="https://orbit.dtu.dk/en/persons/ulla-birgitte-vogel/" class="link"><span> &amp; Vogel, U</span></a> 2022, '<a rel="ContributionToJournal" href="https://orbit.dtu.dk/en/publications/unchanged-pulmonary-toxicity-of-zno-nanoparticles-formulated-in-a/" class="link harvard_title"><span>Unchanged pulmonary toxicity of ZnO nanoparticles formulated in a liquid matrix for glass coating</span></a>', <a rel="Journal" href="#" class="link"><span><em>Nanotoxicology</em></span></a>, vol. 16, no. 6-8, pp. 812-827. <a onclick="window.open(this.href, '_blank','noopener,noreferrer'); return false;" href="https://doi.org/10.1080/17435390.2022.2152751" class="link"><span>https://doi.org/10.1080/17435390.2022.2152751</span></a></div>
            </div>
        
            <div id="cite-standard" class="tab " role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-4" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
                <div class="rendering rendering_researchoutput  rendering_researchoutput_standard rendering_contributiontojournal rendering_standard rendering_contributiontojournal_standard"><a rel="ContributionToJournal" href="https://orbit.dtu.dk/en/publications/unchanged-pulmonary-toxicity-of-zno-nanoparticles-formulated-in-a/" class="link"><span><strong>Unchanged pulmonary toxicity of ZnO nanoparticles formulated in a liquid matrix for glass coating.</strong></span></a> / Saber, Anne Thoustrup<a rel="Person" href="https://orbit.dtu.dk/en/persons/niels-hadrup/" class="link"><span>; Hadrup, Niels</span></a>; Williams, Andrew et al. <br />In: <a rel="Journal" href="#" class="link"><span>Nanotoxicology</span></a>, Vol. 16, No. 6-8, 2022, p. 812-827.<p class="type"><span class="type_family">Research output<span class="type_family_sep">: </span></span><span class="type_classification_parent">Contribution to journal<span class="type_parent_sep"> › </span></span><span class="type_classification">Journal article</span><span class="type_classification"><span class="type_parent_sep"> › </span>Research</span><span class="type_classification"><span class="type_parent_sep"> › </span>peer-review</span></p></div>
            </div>
        
            <div id="cite-RIS" class="tab " role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="tab-5" tabindex="-1" aria-hidden="true">
                <div class="rendering rendering_researchoutput  rendering_researchoutput_ris rendering_contributiontojournal rendering_ris rendering_contributiontojournal_ris"><p>TY  - JOUR</p><p>T1  - Unchanged pulmonary toxicity of ZnO nanoparticles formulated in a liquid matrix for glass coating</p><p>AU  - Saber, Anne Thoustrup</p><p>AU  - Hadrup, Niels</p><p>AU  - Williams, Andrew</p><p>AU  - Mortensen, Alicja</p><p>AU  - Szarek, Jozef</p><p>AU  - Kyjovska, Zdenka</p><p>AU  - Kurz, Alexander</p><p>AU  - Jacobsen, Nicklas Raun</p><p>AU  - Wallin, Håkan</p><p>AU  - Halappanavar, Sabina</p><p>AU  - Vogel, Ulla</p><p>PY  - 2022</p><p>Y1  - 2022</p><p>N2  - The inclusion of nanoparticles can increase the quality of certain products. One application is the inclusion of Zinc oxide (ZnO) nanoparticles in a glass coating matrix to produce a UV-absorbing coating for glass sheets. Yet, the question is whether the inclusion of ZnO in the matrix induces toxicity at low exposure levels. To test this, mice were given single intratracheal instillation of 1) ZnO powder (ZnO), 2) ZnO in a glass matrix coating in its liquid phase (ZnO-Matrix), and 3) the matrix with no ZnO (Matrix). Doses of ZnO were 0.23, 0.67, and 2 µg ZnO/mouse. ZnO Matrix doses had equal amounts of ZnO, while Matrix was adjusted to have an equal volume of matrix as ZnO Matrix. Post-exposure periods were 1, 3, or 28 d. Endpoints were pulmonary inflammation as bronchoalveolar lavage (BAL) fluid cellularity, genotoxicity in lung and liver, measured by comet assay, histopathology of lung and liver, and global gene expression in lung using microarrays. Neutrophil numbers were increased to a similar extent with ZnO and ZnO-Matrix at 1 and 3 d. Only weak genotoxicity without dose-response effects was observed in the lung. Lung histology showed an earlier onset of inflammation in material-exposed groups as compared to controls. Microarray analysis showed a stronger response in terms of the number of differentially regulated genes in ZnO-Matrix exposed mice as compared to Matrix only. Activated canonical pathways included inflammatory and cardiovascular ones. In conclusion, the pulmonary toxicity of ZnO was not changed by formulation in a liquid matrix for glass coating.</p><p>AB  - The inclusion of nanoparticles can increase the quality of certain products. One application is the inclusion of Zinc oxide (ZnO) nanoparticles in a glass coating matrix to produce a UV-absorbing coating for glass sheets. Yet, the question is whether the inclusion of ZnO in the matrix induces toxicity at low exposure levels. To test this, mice were given single intratracheal instillation of 1) ZnO powder (ZnO), 2) ZnO in a glass matrix coating in its liquid phase (ZnO-Matrix), and 3) the matrix with no ZnO (Matrix). Doses of ZnO were 0.23, 0.67, and 2 µg ZnO/mouse. ZnO Matrix doses had equal amounts of ZnO, while Matrix was adjusted to have an equal volume of matrix as ZnO Matrix. Post-exposure periods were 1, 3, or 28 d. Endpoints were pulmonary inflammation as bronchoalveolar lavage (BAL) fluid cellularity, genotoxicity in lung and liver, measured by comet assay, histopathology of lung and liver, and global gene expression in lung using microarrays. Neutrophil numbers were increased to a similar extent with ZnO and ZnO-Matrix at 1 and 3 d. Only weak genotoxicity without dose-response effects was observed in the lung. Lung histology showed an earlier onset of inflammation in material-exposed groups as compared to controls. Microarray analysis showed a stronger response in terms of the number of differentially regulated genes in ZnO-Matrix exposed mice as compared to Matrix only. Activated canonical pathways included inflammatory and cardiovascular ones. In conclusion, the pulmonary toxicity of ZnO was not changed by formulation in a liquid matrix for glass coating.</p><p>KW  - Zinc oxide</p><p>KW  - Comet assay</p><p>KW  - Genotoxicity</p><p>KW  - Advanced materials</p><p>KW  - Gene expression</p><p>U2  - 10.1080/17435390.2022.2152751</p><p>DO  - 10.1080/17435390.2022.2152751</p><p>M3  - Journal article</p><p>C2  - 36480659</p><p>SN  - 1743-5390</p><p>VL  - 16</p><p>SP  - 812</p><p>EP  - 827</p><p>JO  - Nanotoxicology</p><p>JF  - Nanotoxicology</p><p>IS  - 6-8</p><p>ER  - </p></div>
            </div>
        
